I"°<h1 id="colors">Colors</h1>

<p>To define a set of colors in OpenProject, navigate to -&gt; <em>Administration</em> -&gt; <em>Colors</em>.</p>

<p>You can configure a set of predefined colors in OpenProject which you can choose for e.g. <a href="../manage-work-packages/work-package-types/">set colors for work package types</a> or attribute highlighting, e.g. for <a href="../manage-work-packages/work-package-status/">status</a>.</p>

<h2 id="define-a-new-color-in-openproject">Define a new color in OpenProject</h2>

<p>To add a new color, press the green <strong>+ Color</strong> button at the top right.</p>

<p><img src="Sys-admin-colors.png" alt="Sys-admin-colors" /></p>

<ol>
  <li>Add a <strong>name</strong> for your new color.</li>
  <li>Enter the <strong>hexcode</strong> for your new color.</li>
  <li>Press the blue <strong>Save</strong> button.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="Sys-admin-new-color.png" alt="Sys-admin-new-color" /></p>
